		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Fact: ARMv1 and 68k both clocked at 8MHz calculate comparable number of dhrystones per second, despite ARMv1 executing â‰ˆ250% as many instructions. Therefore the ARMv1 must be doing 50% the work per instruction.<br /><br />If you want to see how this is true, you need to actually look at the sequence of instructions that are used in the dhrystone benchmark on these two machines, not just look at the available instructions.

		

